g5rPADK2vJ0-AshJGuSGGs6_HeJcSJd3FEV23mxZLCLmNB8dz8VlnncPex62SWGXH-4s-olSUjmw=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Refining test procedures**\\n\\nI need to refine the existing tests without running them. It looks like addInputHandler and class$ are not covered. I’m wondering if our prior startAnt path overlooked addInputHandler due to projectHelp? It should actually addInputHandler before projectHelp. There might be issues with System.exit interception and the SecurityManager. Maybe our dynamic report is from the JVM, and we need to ensure addInputHandler is reachable without System.exit. I'm realizing addInputHandler occurs before projectHelp config, so there’s some uncertainty about the test runs.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining startAnt test issues**\\n\\nIt seems the startAnt test may have been skipped due to installSecurityManagerIfSupported being false, potentially in a native image or because the test didn’t compile. I might need an update to access private addInputHandler directly without using reflection. While startAnt is public, it exits early if the security manager isn’t supported. The report suggests it wasn’t covered, possibly due to issues with JVM security manager installation. If I could use Process to run Main in a forked JVM, I wonder if coverage would be counted. This is tricky!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing addInputHandler accessibility**\\n\\nI'm considering whether it's acceptable that the public API doesn’t expose addInputHandler. I definitely need coverage here. Testing a private method directly through reflection might not be allowed, so maybe creating a subclass would work? I could also explore preventing System.exit by throwing an Error from a custom SecurityManager, but startAnt only catches Throwable in processArgs. After that, System.exit isn’t wrapped in a try-except, meaning it would propagate. Our exception extends SecurityException, not Error — yet the catch blocks around runBuild do capture Throwable. This is tricky!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_mLTdZQYNiI39gcp4tRA1YKuS|fc_034814c5435b4cdc0169f548ad07c481a28ae2f8604ed5b89e", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge10/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/ant/ant/1.6/main/extracted/main/org/apache/tools/ant/Main.java", "offset": 830, "limit": 80}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 26924, "output": 1009, "cacheRead": 6144, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34077, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777682585263, "responseId": "resp_034814c5435b4cdc0169f5489a31fc81a2b2d6ed1218cc5b18"}}
