PADK2vJ0-AshJGuSGGs6_HeJcSJd3FEV23mxZLCLmNB8dz8VlnncPex62SWGXH-4s-olSUjmw=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Refining test procedures**\\n\\nI need to refine the existing tests without running them. It looks like addInputHandler and class$ are not covered. I’m wondering if our prior startAnt path overlooked addInputHandler due to projectHelp? It should actually addInputHandler before projectHelp. There might be issues with System.exit interception and the SecurityManager. Maybe our dynamic report is from the JVM, and we need to ensure addInputHandler is reachable without System.exit. I'm realizing addInputHandler occurs before projectHelp config, so there’s some uncertainty about the test runs.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining startAnt test issues**\\n\\nIt seems the startAnt test may have been skipped due to installSecurityManagerIfSupported being false, potentially in a native image or because the test didn’t compile. I might need an update to access private addInputHandler directly without using reflection. While startAnt is public, it exits early if the security manager isn’t supported. The report suggests it wasn’t covered, possibly due to issues with JVM security manager installation. If I could use Process to run Main in a forked JVM, I wonder if coverage would be counted. This is tricky!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing addInputHandler accessibility**\\n\\nI'm considering whether it's acceptable that the public API doesn’t expose addInputHandler. I definitely need coverage here. Testing a private method directly through reflection might not be allowed, so maybe creating a subclass would work? I could also explore preventing System.exit by throwing an Error from a custom SecurityManager, but startAnt only catches Throwable in processArgs. After that, System.exit isn’t wrapped in a try-except, meaning it would propagate. Our exception extends SecurityException, not Error — yet the catch blocks around runBuild do capture Throwable. This is tricky!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_mLTdZQYNiI39gcp4tRA1YKuS|fc_034814c5435b4cdc0169f548ad07c481a28ae2f8604ed5b89e", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge10/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/ant/ant/1.6/main/extracted/main/org/apache/tools/ant/Main.java", "offset": 830, "limit": 80}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 26924, "output": 1009, "cacheRead": 6144, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34077, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777682585263, "responseId": "resp_034814c5435b4cdc0169f5489a31fc81a2b2d6ed1218cc5b18"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_mLTdZQYNiI39gcp4tRA1YKuS|fc_034814c5435b4cdc0169f548ad07c481a28ae2f8604ed5b89e", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * Prints the Ant version information to <code>System.out</code>.\r\n     *\r\n     * @exception BuildException if the version information is unavailable\r\n     */\r\n    private static void printVersion() throws BuildException {\r\n        System.out.println(getAntVersion());\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * Cache of the Ant version information when it has been loaded.\r\n     */\r\n    private static String antVersion = null;\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * Returns the Ant version information, if available. Once the information\r\n     * has been loaded once, it's cached and returned from the cache on future\r\n     * calls.\r\n     *\r\n     * @return the Ant version information as a String\r\n     *         (always non-<code>null</code>)\r\n     *\r\n     * @exception BuildException if the version information is unavailable\r\n     */\r\n    public static synchronized String getAntVersion() throws BuildException {\r\n        if (antVersion == null) {\r\n            try {\r\n                Properties props = new Properties();\r\n                InputStream in =\r\n                    Main.class.getResourceAsStream(\"/org/apache/tools/ant/version.txt\");\r\n                props.load(in);\r\n                in.close();\r\n\r\n                StringBuffer msg = new StringBuffer();\r\n                msg.append(\"Apache Ant version \");\r\n                msg.append(props.getProperty(\"VERSION\"));\r\n                msg.append(\" compiled on \");\r\n                msg.append(props.getProperty(\"DATE\"));\r\n                antVersion = msg.toString();\r\n            } catch (IOException ioe) {\r\n                throw new BuildException(\"Could not load the version information:\"\r\n                                         + ioe.getMessage());\r\n            } catch (NullPointerException npe) {\r\n                throw new BuildException(\"Could not load the version information.\");\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        return antVersion;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n     /**\r\n      * Prints the description of a project (if there is one) to\r\n      * <code>System.out</code>.\r\n      *\r\n      * @param project The project to display a description of.\r\n      *                Must not be <code>null</code>.\r\n      */\r\n    private static void printDescription(Project project) {\r\n       if (project.getDescription() != null) {\r\n          project.log(project.getDescription());\r\n       }\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * Prints a list of all targets in the specified project to\r\n     * <code>System.out</code>, optionally including subtargets.\r\n     *\r\n     * @param project The project to display a description of.\r\n     *                Must not be <code>null</code>.\r\n     * @param printSubTargets Whether or not subtarget names should also be\r\n     *                        printed.\r\n     */\r\n    private static void printTargets(Project project, boolean printSubTargets) {\r\n        // find the target with the longest name\r\n        int maxLength = 0;\r\n        Enumeration ptargets = project.getTargets().elements();\r\n        String targetName;\r\n        String targetDescription;\r\n        Target currentTarget;\r\n\n[110 more lines in file. Use offset=910 to continue.]"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777682605500}]}
